org.rsna.ctp.pipeline

Class QueueManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.pipeline.QueueManager

  • public class QueueManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A class to manage a queue directory and multiple subdirectories to prevent any subdirectory from growing larger than a specified size. The files stored in the queue are placed at the deepest level of the tree, with higher-level directories being used just to store directories.

    • Constructor Detail

      • QueueManager

        public QueueManager(java.io.File root,
            int nLevels,
            int maxSize)
        Create a QueueManager for a root directory.
        Parameters:
        root - the root directory of the queue tree. If the root directory does not exist, it is created.
        nLevels - number of levels in the queue tree. If specified to be less than 3, it is set to 3.
        maxSize - the maximum number of files allowed in any directory (except for the root directory). If specified to be less than 200, it is set to 200.

        Parameters:
        file - the file to be inserted.
        Returns:
        a File pointing to the object in the queue or null if the file had zero length.

      • enqueueDir

        public int enqueueDir(java.io.File dir)
        Insert all the files in a directory into the queue directory tree, preserving the embedded filename, if present. This method does not walk a deep tree; it only takes the first-generation children of the specified directory, ignoring any child directories. This method deletes any files that it enqueues from the original directory.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory whose contents are to be inserted.
        Returns:
        the number of files actually enqueued from the directory.

      • dequeue

        public java.io.File dequeue(java.io.File dir)
        Retrieve a file from the queue directory tree. The file is removed from the queue and placed into a directory supplied by the calling method. Files are returned in FIFO order unless files have been placed into queue directories by hand, in which case those files are likely to be served first.
        Parameters:
        dir - the directory into which to place the file to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        a File pointing to the file in the supplied directory. If no file is available in the queue, null is returned. If the supplied directory file is null or not a directory, null is returned.

      • peek

        public java.io.File peek()
        Find the next file in the queue directory tree without removing it from the queue.
        Returns:
        a File pointing to the file in the supplied directory. If no file is available in the queue, null is returned. If the supplied directory file is null or not a directory, null is returned.

      • recount

        public int recount()
        Re-count all the files in the queue.
        Returns:
        the number of files in the queue.
